  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Save Somali Refugee Children from Malnutrition</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Described as &quot;the worst humanitarian disaster in the world&quot; by the UN Refugee Agency, the famine in Somalia is estimated to affect nearly half the Somali population - 3.7 million people. Tens of thousands have died; the majority were children. 

They arrive at UNHCR camps exhausted, dehydrated and malnourished. Up to 50% of children suffer from severe malnutrition. They urgently need medicine, high-protein and high-energy food, clean water, shelter and other basic services.</narrative>
  </description>
